DynamicHandler.Name: Wms Server from Kml Files
DynamicHandler.Decription:
This HttpHandler runs a Wms Server based on Sharpmap, with layers loaded from local Kml Files.
<Warning> A set of assemblies from Sharpmap and dependencies need to be added to the DNN bin folder for the handler to be functional. Because of the regular cap of 8Mo in DNN extension packages, those libraries have to be downloaded manually. You can find them in the source file tree: https://ariciepkp.codeplex.com/SourceControl/latest#Libraries/
<Warning 2> If you have request caps configured in your firewall, such as with the default protection rule against denial of service, you should update those caps, especially if you are to consume that WMS service with a small image tiles size configured on the client side, because they will generate a lot of Http request to your handler, which might result in the client getting banned.
<TODO:> Update the WMS service description parameter, upload your KML files to your DNN instance and update the corresponding list parameter.

VariableInfo.Name: WmsDescriptionImport
VariableInfo.Decription: This is a Json representation of an object of type WmsServiceDescription to be configured into the Wms service handler. An object of type TokenizedTextInfo is used to inject the wms url at runtime.

TokenizedTextInfo.Text: { "Abstract": "", "AccessConstraints": "", "ContactInformation": { "Address": { "Address": null, "AddressType": null, "City": null, "Country": null, "PostCode": null, "StateOrProvince": null }, "ElectronicMailAddress": null, "FacsimileTelephone": null, "PersonPrimary": { "Organisation": null, "Person": null }, "Position": null, "VoiceTelephone": null }, "Fees": "", "Keywords": [], "LayerLimit": 0, "MaxHeight": 0, "MaxWidth": 0, "OnlineResource": "Test OnlineResource", "Title": "Test Title", "PublicAccessURL": null }

VariableInfo.Name: KmlFileList
VariableInfo.Decription: This is a list of local KML files to your dnn install. In order to use the selector, you may have to allow the corresponding file extension in the Host settings. You can also use a relative path as in the provided example.

VariableInfo.Name: PixelSensitivity
VariableInfo.Decription: When using the GetFeatureInfo method from the WMS service, the server will query and return the records around a targeted area. This parameter defines the precision of that intersection query in pixels of the Viewport. Note that the usual GetMap method that produce image tiles does not make us of that parameter.

ActionProviderSettingsOfSimpleEngineEven.Name: Create Sharpmap Wms Context
ActionProviderSettingsOfSimpleEngineEven.Decription: Sharpmap can create a dedicated Wms Context from the standard HttpContext object available in our HttpHandler.

VariableInfo.Name: context
VariableInfo.Decription: the Wms Context class constructor takes an instance of HttpContext as parameter. The Request's HttpContext is available execution context with a Flee Expression.

ActionProviderSettingsOfSimpleEngineEven.Name: Load WmsDescriptionImport from parameter
ActionProviderSettingsOfSimpleEngineEven.Decription: Because the corresponding sharpmap type does not have properties to build the corresponding user interface, a json export is used instead, with the additional benefit that token replace eases the injection of dynamic content in the wms service description fields. Update the corresponding parameter accordingly.

ActionProviderSettingsOfSimpleEngineEven.Name: Build Map with Kml Files
ActionProviderSettingsOfSimpleEngineEven.Decription:
The Sharpmap Map object is central in loading, querying and rendering GIS content. Sharpmap Wms component deal with rendering a given Map object. We first need to build that object with individual layers loaded from Kml Files.
Caching is used for each KmlProvider loaded from an individual file, and the default zoom is set to 110% of the map extents.

ActionProviderSettingsOfSimpleEngineEven.Name: For Each Kml File, add a layer to the map
Pass the arguments to Sharpmap WmsServer
ActionProviderSettingsOfSimpleEngineEven.Decription: The WmsServer class has a method that takes the parameters previously created and builds the appropriate text based or image based HttpResponse. Note that because of a possible thread aborting exception, exceptions logging was disabled for that individual action.

ActionProviderConfigOfSimpleEngineEvent.Name: Return Rest Operation Action

ActionProviderConfigOfSimpleEngineEvent.Name: Deserialize Action Provider

ActionProviderConfigOfSimpleEngineEvent.Decription: Displays a DNN message with token replace on the current page. A target module can be optionnally chosen.

ActionProviderConfigOfSimpleEngineEvent.Name: File Manager Action

ActionProviderConfigOfSimpleEngineEvent.Name: File Read Action
ActionProviderConfigOfSimpleEngineEvent.Decription: This provider allows to read a file to a given String variable, given its path by dynamic expressions

ActionProviderConfigOfSimpleEngineEvent.Name: File Write Action
ActionProviderConfigOfSimpleEngineEvent.Decription: This provider allows to write a content to a file, given its path and the content to write by dynamic expressions

ActionProviderConfigOfSimpleEngineEvent.Name: Object Action
ActionProviderConfigOfSimpleEngineEvent.Decription: This provider allows to do actions on object by setting properties, calling methods or hooking event handlers

ActionProviderConfigOfSimpleEngineEvent.Name: Log Event Action

ActionProviderConfigOfSimpleEngineEvent.Name: Loop
ActionProviderConfigOfSimpleEngineEvent.Decription: This provider allows to loop running a sub bot over a custom collection. On each run, the current item of the collection is affected to a custom variable.

ActionProviderConfigOfSimpleEngineEvent.Name: Multiple Action Provider
ActionProviderConfigOfSimpleEngineEvent.Decription: Runs sub sequences of Actions

ActionProviderConfigOfSimpleEngineEvent.Name: Object Actions Provider
ActionProviderConfigOfSimpleEngineEvent.Decription: This provider allows to call object methods or set object properties

ActionProviderConfigOfSimpleEngineEvent.Name: Load Profile Property

ActionProviderConfigOfSimpleEngineEvent.Name: Save Profile Property
ActionProviderConfigOfSimpleEngineEvent.Decription: This provider allows to save an identity or personnalization profile property for a given user.

ActionProviderConfigOfSimpleEngineEvent.Name: Redirect Action

ActionProviderConfigOfSimpleEngineEvent.Name: Run Program Action

ActionProviderConfigOfSimpleEngineEvent.Decription: This provider allows to run a sub-bot as a dedicated action. Because of the sequential nature of the engine, the subbot triggers each previous step up to the current step, the rules and action should be configured accordingly

ActionProviderConfigOfSimpleEngineEvent.Name: Web Action

ActionProviderConfigOfSimpleEngineEvent.Name: While Action Provider
ActionProviderConfigOfSimpleEngineEvent.Decription: This provider allows to loop running a sub bot while a boolean condition evaluates to true.
